OnlyaJedi 23-Nov-21 11:24 AM
Short answer - it's complicated. Long answer - it's really complicated, in that you really can't divide the versions of World of Darkness into editions like they do for Dungeons and Dragons, even though the publishers try to (that's why hers lists itself as 5th ed.)
11:25
I'll try to get a more cohesive answer in a moment, after I find the info.
Pulse [Allison] 23-Nov-21 11:26 AM
Thanks!
OnlyaJedi 23-Nov-21 11:26 AM
Dungeons and Dragons has always been owned by a company that has published it with the intent to revise it with a plan. World of Darkness has been bought and sold a couple of times and it's gotten a little messed up.
11:29
Vampire the Masquerade came out in 1991 and the associated other books (for Mage, Werewolf, mortals, etc) came out in the following years. They also released a Vampire: The Dark Ages book in the late 90s that let you play a Vampire character in, well, the Dark Ages. However, it also changed a bunch of rules and so was kinda a second edition (the 1991 edition is the one I grew up playing). Then the 2004 edition came out (that's the one we play) and was sometimes called New World of Darkness and then later called Chronicles of Darkness. That's the one I bought into and started running games for in college.
11:31
Then, they re-released Chronicles of Darkness, called it that for sure, but in the re-release changed a whole bunch of rules again. I didn't like that version at all and never played it or bought it. That's either 3rd or 4th ed., depending on who you talk to.
11:33
Then, the whole thing was bought out sometime in the mid-2010s. Video games were made again, people got interested in it again - I was shocked! And then they started releasing new versions of the game again, but using the old naming conventions like Vampire the Masquerade, which was confusing. So technically thats either 4th or 5th ed, again depending on who you ask. Honestly, it could be first ed. in my mind. The whole thing is a hot mess
11:34
I wouldn't touch the new stuff with a 30ft pole, because of the way the buyout happened, but I'm old and crotchety. See the picture above^^^
